Place @ground beef{10%ounce}, @Mediterranean spice blend{2%tsp}, @feta cheese{2%tbsp}, and @hot sauce{1/2%tsp} in a large #bowl{} (save the rest of the spice, feta, and hot sauce for later). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix until combined. Shape into two ½-inch-thick patties and set aside.

Wash and dry all produce. Zest @lemon{1}, then cut into quarters. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}. Heat a #grill{} over direct heat and brush grates with @vegetable oil{2%tsp}.

> TIP: If cooking indoors, heat a drizzle of oil and 1 TBSP butter in a grill pan or large pan over medium-high heat.

Add patties to grill or pan and cook until marks appear on bottom, ~{7-8%minutes}. Flip and cook until marks appear on other side, ~{6-7%minutes} more. Transfer to a #plate{}. Meanwhile, mix together @sour cream{2%tbsp}, a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp}, remaining Mediterranean spice blend, and remaining @feta cheese{1/2%cup} in a small bowl. Set aside.

Trim @Persian cucumber{2} ends, then quarter lengthwise. Cut crosswise into ½-inch pieces. Quarter @Roma tomato{2}, then dice into ½-inch pieces. In a medium bowl, toss together cucumbers, tomatoes, half the shallot (add more for extra onion-y flavor), lemon zest, juice from two lemon quarters, @Dijon mustard{1%tsp} (we sent more), a large drizzle olive oil, and @sugar{1%tsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

Microwave @butter{1%tbsp} in a small, #microwave-safe bowl{} until melted, about ~{20%seconds}. Split @brioche buns{2} in half and brush cut sides with melted butter. Place on grill or in pan used for burgers cut-side down and toast until light golden, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Spread sour cream mixture onto bottom halves of buns, then place patties on top. Top with remaining bun halves. Sprinkle over remaining hot sauce, if desired. Divide between plates. Serve with salad and remaining lemon on the side.

> TIP: Put a little salad inside your burger for a cool, crisp sensation.